
OpenVAS (Greenbone Vulnerability Manager)

1. Overview
OpenVAS is a free, open-source vulnerability scanner used for network and web application scanning.  
It is the main component of the Greenbone Vulnerability Management (GVM) framework.

Used in:
- Network security assessments  
- Vulnerability scanning  
- Compliance checking  
- Open-source alternative to Nessus  

---

2. Key Features
- Fully open-source  
- Large vulnerability feed  
- Web UI (GSA) + CLI tools  
- Scheduled scans  
- Custom scan configurations  
- Credentialed scans  

---

3. Installation
Kali Linux (pre-installed)
sudo gvm-setup
sudo gvm-check-setup
sudo gvm-start
Debian/Ubuntu
sudo apt install gvm
sudo gvm-setup

Access the Web UI
https://127.0.0.1:9392

---

4. Important Components
Component	Description
gvmd	Manager daemon
openvas-scanner	Scanner engine
gsad	Web UI
GVM Feed	Vulnerability updates

---

5. Important Parameters / Scan Settings
Setting	Description
Port list	Full scan / TCP only / custom
Alive test	ARP / ICMP / TCP SYN
Scan Config	Full & Fast / Full & Deep
Overrides	Manage false positives

----

6. Advanced Usage
CLI Scan Example
omp -u admin -w password -T           

Update Feeds
sudo greenbone-feed-sync
